In this course the main concepts, theories and basics of management are covered. Participants learn to understand the functions of management and the characteristics, skills, types and roles of manager. In addition, the basics of organizational theory, organizational design, the topics of organizational communication and communication climate are unfolded. During the course participants learn how to analyze and apply management theories in practice. Furthermore, students will learn how to identify managerial issues and suggest solutions to them.Objectives/eesmärkid:  In this course you will gain basic knowledge of management theories, organizational design and organizational communication which will help you to understand and solve important managerial questions.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course is passed the participant understands:
*	management theories and can see how introduced theories apply in the management of modern organizations;
*	content and the role of management in directing organizational activities
*	issues of organizations management.
*	knows and distinguishes different management basic functions (planning, organizing, controlling, leadership, communication and decision making) 
*	the importance in management as a whole
*	the role of the manager in organization
*	the main issues of organizational design and structure.
